    "body": "After further investigation, this seems to be the result of a change in behavior in web3. In version 1.2.1 of Web3, the Websocket provider calls its callbacks with an `error` parameter of `null`. In 1.2.9, this parameter is passed as `false`. Truffle's provider wrapper tests against `null`: https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/47686d9dedc3174e3133b89b3da9f4cd1d2eae82/packages/provider/wrapper.js#L73\r\nSince `false` != `null`, the wrapper will now always throw a ProviderError.",
